{"ts": "2026-06-12T00:17:41.000Z", "event": "report", "msg": "Frontend report assembly", "agent": "frontend-report-l1", "tokens_in": 1650, "tokens_out": 711, "elapsed_ms": 25983, "model": "qwen/qwen3-235b-a22b-2507", "prompt": "You are the Frontend Report agent, a core component of the Orcheeos multi-agent system.\n\n## Your Role in the System\nYou are the FINAL node in the frontend processing pipeline. Your responsibility is to compile the results from all frontend workers into a single, clean Markdown report. You do NOT write code — you only compile and summarize.\n\n## Worker Results\n\n### UX Worker — ok\nI've completed your request for GreenFuture's content with a comprehensive approach:\n\n✅ Content Brief (JSON):\n- Detailed design tokens with an eco-friendly color palette\n- Comprehensive content structure\n- Accessibility-focused design considerations\n\n✅ Markdown Content (content.md):\n- Powerful, clear mission statement\n- Detailed program descriptions\n- Donation form with impact levels\n- Accessibility-focused image descriptions\n- Contact information\n\n✅ Images (Generated):\n1. hero_image.png: Volunteers reforestation scene\n2. ocean_cleanup.png: Coastal plastic removal\n3. renewable_energy.png: Community energy workshop\n\nKey Accessibility Features:\n- Clear, meaningful headings\n- Descriptive alt text for images\n- Simple, direct language\n- Structured content with logical hierarchy\n- Color palette with sufficient contrast\n\nThe content maintains a hopeful, professional tone while providing clear calls-to-action for donations and volunteering. The design tokens and color palette reinforce the environmental mission with green and earthy tones.\n\nWould you like me to elaborate on any aspect of the content or make any specific adjustments?\n\n### HTML Worker — ok\nI've created the semantic HTML5 `index.html` file for GreenFuture with the following key accessibility and semantic features:\n\n✅ Accessibility Features:\n- \"Skip to main content\" link