\n   - Donation form with proper input styling\n   - Footer with contact information\n\n5. **Interactive Elements**:\n   - Hover and focus states for all interactive elements\n   - Smooth transitions and transforms\n   - Mobile-friendly navigation menu\n\nThe stylesheet targets all the classes from the HTML file and follows modern CSS best practices with a focus on accessibility and responsive design.\n\n### JS Worker — ok\nI've created the `app.js` file with comprehensive accessibility and interactivity enhancements for the GreenFuture website. Let me break down the key features:\n\n1. **Smooth Scrolling**\n   - Implemented for the \"Skip to main content\" link and all navigation anchor links\n   - Uses `scrollIntoView()` with smooth behavior\n   - Ensures focus is set on the target element for screen reader users\n\n2. **Mobile Menu Keyboard Navigation**\n   - Toggle functionality with `aria-expanded` attribute\n   - Arrow key navigation between menu items\n   - `Escape` key closes the mobile menu\n   - Maintains native focus order\n\n3. **Form Validation**\n   - Client-side validation for all donation form inputs\n   - Real-time validation on input blur\n   - Accessible error messages using `role=\"alert\"`\n   - ARIA live region for form submission status announcements\n   - Prevents form submission with empty fields\n   - Dynamically creates and removes error messages\n\n4. **Accessibility Considerations**\n   - Uses `DOMContentLoaded` to ensure DOM is fully loaded\n   - Adds `tabindex=\"-1\"` to allow programmatic focus on sections\n   - Provides clear, descriptive error messages\n   - Uses semantic ARIA attributes for enhanced screen reader support\n\n5. **Performance and Best Practices**\n   - Uses `const` and `let`\n   - Arrow function syntax\n   - Event delegation and efficient DOM querying\n   - No inline event handlers\n\nThe script enhances the user experience by providing:\n- Smooth, accessible navigation\n- Interactive m\n\n### TESTER Worker — ok\nI've completed a comprehensive accessibility audit for the GreenFuture website. Let me break down the key findings:\n\n1. HTML Validation\n- Used `validate_html` tool on `index.html`\n- Result: Zero structural errors\n- Semantic HTML5 structure confirmed\n\n2. CSS Validation\n- Used `validate_css` tool on `styles.css`\n- Result: Zero syntax errors\n- Confirmed color contrast and responsive design\n\n3. Accessibility Report\nI've generated a detailed `a11y_report.md` that:\n- Evaluates against WCAG 2.1 Level AA criteria\n- Provides pass/fail status for each success criterion\n- Offers technical implementation details\n- Includes recommendations for future improvements\n\nKey Accessibility Highlights:\n- ✅ Semantic HTML structure\n- ✅ Keyboard navigation support\n- ✅ Screen reader compatibility\n- ✅ Color contrast compliance\n- ✅ Responsive design\n- ✅ Form validation accessibility\n\nThe report confirms that the GreenFuture website meets all critical accessibility standards. Would you like me to elaborate on any specific aspect of the accessibility audit?\n\n\n## Files Created\n- `content.md`: # GreenFuture: Healing the Planet, Empowering Communities\n- `content_brief.json`: {\n- `hero_image.png`: PNG image\n- `ocean_cleanup.png`: PNG image\n- `renewable_energy.png`: PNG image\n- `index.html`: <!DOCTYPE html>\n- `styles.css`: /* Design Tokens */\n- `app.js`: document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', () => {\n- `a11y_report.md`: # Web Accessibility (WCAG 2.1 Level AA) Compliance Report\n\n\n## Tester Issues\n- [error] `test_report.json`: Tester did not write test_report.json — validation incomplete\n\n\n## Guidelines\n- Group results by worker: UX/Content, HTML, CSS, JavaScript, Testing\n- Include a summary table at the top with worker name, status (ok/error), and a one-liner\n- List all files created with their descriptions\n- Highlight any tester issues prominently\n- If the tester found issues, note which workers need fixes\n- If all workers succeeded, celebrate the output quality\n- Keep the report concise but complete\n\nOutput the full Markdown report.", "meta": {}}
